    "body": "@Duanraudon, follow the link @Zachinquarantine shared above should help solve this issue.\r\nor, find practical instructions here: https://notes.ethereum.org/@launchpad/ropsten\r\nor [here](https://github.com/xhyumiracle/eth2launch), a docker-compose file I just wrote for `sepolia` full node at post-merge stage. Although it's not for ropsten, you got the basic idea.\r\n\r\nBasically, geth is only a EL client, you need to run a CL client and connect it to EL the client through local rpc after the merge, as mentioned by @Zachinquarantine. Running EL client only would yield the error msg you encountered.",
